synopses.synopsis: Part situation-comedy and part variety format, The Abbott and Costello Show was a relatively long-running hit on radio. Besides Bud Abbott and Lou Costello's usual double-talk routines, which they had perfected in vaudeville, the half-hour program featured singers Marilyn Maxwell and Connie Haines, the comic talents of screen tough girl Irish Adrian and comedian Sid Fields, and the formidable voice versatility of actor Mel Blanc.
